<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Good Info! I would recomend that to anyone interested in guilds!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Azuth">Azuth</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:27 a.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Good Info! I would recomend that to anyone interested in guilds!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=8" TARGET=_self>Guides: Finding a guild, Creating a guild, Guild Leadership and more...</A> (Brimstone)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> To All People: In a guild, Leading a guild,

<BR>&gt; or Looking for a guild
<P>&gt; [The following guides and articles pertain
<BR>&gt; to ANY online gaming clan, guild, order,
<BR>&gt; etc. There are *some* references to Ultima
<BR>&gt; Online and EverQuest, and one of the guides
<BR>&gt; focuses heavily on the Ultima Online
<BR>&gt; universe, however, can be modified for any
<BR>&gt; OnlineRPG (Guide: Organized Guild Warfare
<BR>&gt; ).
<P>&gt; The other guides, in my opinion, are a must
<BR>&gt; read for anyone who wishes to Lead or Form a
<BR>&gt; guild, Needs help with creating a voting
<BR>&gt; system for new members, needs help with
<BR>&gt; creating policies for membership, or is
<BR>&gt; looking to JOIN or FIND a guild! I have
<BR>&gt; spent hours creating the following guides,
<BR>&gt; and the feedback from those who have read
<BR>&gt; them has been all positive.
<P>&gt; I have heard many guilds say that from now
<BR>&gt; on, they will request that all new members
<BR>&gt; read the Guide for Finding a Guild. This
<BR>&gt; guide is VERY helpful for getting players
<BR>&gt; who seek a guild into the proper state of
<BR>&gt; mind.
<P>&gt; Without wasting anymore time, let me give
<BR>&gt; you the links to the Guides/Articles I have
<BR>&gt; written for the players of online games,
<BR>&gt; more specifically, Guilds:
<P>&gt; Guides and Articles for Guilds and Players
<BR>&gt; The Foundation and Birth of your Guild
<BR>&gt; Guide to Finding the Perfect Guild
<BR>&gt; Voting System
<BR>&gt; Being a Leader
<BR>&gt; Sample Policy
<BR>&gt; Organized Guild Warfare
<P>&gt; All of the above mentioned guides will help
<BR>&gt; to promote healthy, sociable, fun, BONDING
<BR>&gt; guilds and players. That is what online
<BR>&gt; gaming is all about, fun and respect. If you
<BR>&gt; can help me by posting some (or all) of
<BR>&gt; these articles on your web pages, I think
<BR>&gt; that we would see a lot more guilds who
<BR>&gt; focused on healthy roleplaying and PVP, as
<BR>&gt; opposed to much of the crap we see today in
<BR>&gt; online games. I personally will be asking
<BR>&gt; that all new recruits for LOA read the Guide
<BR>&gt; to finding a guild, even if it sways his/her
<BR>&gt; choice for a guild.
<P>&gt; Thanks again, everyone, for your support and
<BR>&gt; kind words regarding my articles.
<P>&gt; Brimstone ,
<BR>&gt; Lost Order of Akalabeth ,
<BR>&gt; Founding Father and Chancellor of
<BR>&gt; Communication
<BR>&gt; ICQ - 206317
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
